&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About your skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Revenue Accounting savvy: You understand ASC 606 and SaaS revenue holistically and the key fundamentals. You are able read a subscription revenue contract and identify the key accounting issues within the terms and conditions. You understand the concept of stand-alone selling price and the allocation of revenue between multiple performance obligation arrangements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Accounting System guru: You are experienced with Netsuite Advanced Revenue Module. You understand how to process revenue transactions in Netsuite. You understand how to reconcile revenue transactions from our subledger to general ledger in Netsuite.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Communication: You raise your hands when you need help, find an issue or want to bounce ideas off. You understand accounting is not just an Excel spreadsheet and reconciliation. The key to success in our role at Udemy is to communicate, to ask questions and to work with all parts of the organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team Player: You understand that our work and responsibility in the company is fluid and not static. We put up projects and tasks to get to the next level as a team. We put in extra effort to support a launch of a new product or process. We also celebrate and take a moment to enjoy what we achieved as a team. You are excited at the sound of these opportunities and partake in these new projects!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
