&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Your Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enterprise Renewal Ownership: You independently manage high-value, complex books of business from early engagement through to close. You confidently lead high-stakes conversations across pricing, contracting, and procurement, expertly balancing ARR protection and contract quality with customer trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Forecasting Discipline: You possess a deep understanding of SaaS metrics (including ARR, GRR, NRR, and churn) and leverage this knowledge to maintain an accurate, objective rolling forecast. You clearly communicate pipeline movement, risk, and expected outcomes to leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cross-Functional Influence: You partner seamlessly across Sales, Customer Success, Legal, Deal Desk, and Finance to drive alignment and navigate ambiguity. You effectively execute complex renewal strategies and drive initiatives to completion without relying on direct authority.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Analytical Problem Solving: You excel at evaluating complex retention data to identify root causes of churn risk, translating insights into actionable recommendations. Additionally, you develop talent through mentorship and feedback, creating a culture of clarity and accountability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
